The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Friday, December 27, 2002  Shining Jewel, River Melody triumph 
 BY STAR RACER				 										Calcutta: The two hot-favourites, and both Sizzling Melody progenies  River Melody and Shining Jewel  landed their respective events, the 1,200m Army Cup and the 2,000m General A. S. Vaidya Memorial Cup, at the RCTC Thursday. However, jockey Mark Gallagher had to stretch out the Daniel David-filly River Melody to win the race from Callisto, while Vijay Singhs ward Shining Jewel simply cantered home in the hands of jockey Cristopher Alford.
